-- South Africa Wants State Companies More Integrated in Government Programs
-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d
-- 2010-09-23T06:18:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/south-africa-wants-state-companies-more-integrated-in-government-programs.html
South Africa is attempting to
integrate state-owned companies with government operations in
order to allow it to use resources for its programs more easily,
Collins Chabane, minister in the presidency, told reporters
today in Durban.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Franz Wild in Durban at 
 fwild@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  